<p>Today on The Survival Podcast I take your calls on real estate, education, radios, swales,  toxic plants, tactical kit, wood sheds, shotguns, ammo, bamboo, finance, vehicle preps  and more.</p>
<p>Remember to be on a show like this one just pick up your phone and call <strong><span style="color: #800000;">866-65-THINK</span></strong>. The best way to improve your chances of being on the air is ask your question or make your point up front, then provide details.</p>
<p>Also please do your best to call from a quiet area with a good connection and speak up so you can be well heard.</p>
<p>While I can’t put all calls on the air but I do my best to get as many of them on as I can.</p>
<p><strong><span style="color: #800000;">Join Me Today As I Respond to Your Calls and Discuss&#8230;</span></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Waterways on BOLs good or bad or some of both</li>
<li>The dumbest reason I have ever heard for the failure of our school systems</li>
<li>Putting a CB antenna in your attic</li>
<li>The structure and shape of <a target="_blank" title="swale" href="http://tspwiki.com/index.php?title=Swale">swale</a> berms and why it matters</li>
<li>Why black poly tanks for water tanks</li>
<li>Mountain laurel and other toxic plants</li>
<li>Thoughts on tactical kit for your firearms training</li>
<li>Advice on building a wood shed from <a target="_blank" title="Ben Falk" href="http://tspwiki.com/index.php?title=Ben_Falk">Ben Falk</a></li>
<li>What color of <a target="_blank" title="shotgun" href="http://tspwiki.com/index.php?title=Shotgun">shotgun</a> for <a target="_blank" title="home defense" href="http://tspwiki.com/index.php?title=Home_defense#Home_Security">home defense</a>, hunter brown or evil black</li>
<li>Does properly stored ammo have a shelf life</li>
<li>An urban legend about ammo primer shelf life that is total BULLSHIT!</li>
<li>Thoughts on bamboo for prepping, <a title="homesteading" href="http://www.thesurvivalpodcast.com/from-home-to-homestead">homesteading</a> and controlling spread</li>
<li>Council member Jon Pugliano on high frequency trading and the BS around it</li>
<li>Brand new cars with no spare tire, yep, just wow!</li>
</ul>
<p><strong><span style="color: #800000;">Resources for today’s show…</span></strong></p>
<ul>
