		<div class="comment-body"><p>This is my thoughts.</p>
<p>I will make the argument that if you are no longer in charge of keeping it in control, it could (will) spread out and go on, like any other species considered &#8220;invasive&#8221;. I&#8217;m a bit meh to that argument though.</p>
<p>I have seen some areas around here where there used to be a little bit of bamboo, but the person long since left and now its ALOT of bamboo.  I am like 99% sure i&#8221;m going to be buying Moso bamboo. It&#8217;s just too impressive of a timber bamboo not to get, and there is a nursery about 30 minutes down the road that sells it. After seeing it, i&#8217;m totally sold.</p>
<p>We&#8217;re in the process of planting 30 (clumping) bamboo plants right now along our southern edge so that we can get a very heavy wind and sound break. Right now we definitely need it with this storm coming. I&#8217;m sure my garden and young trees are getting beat to death right now.</p>
</div>

