		<div class="comment-body"><p>On the right track for sure.  </p>
<p>Here is my method teach them how to learn, how to read, write, do math, and science basics as you say.</p>
<p>Then NO CONTROLS, let them take it from there.  Instead of teaching the origins of man, ask them to figure it out, cut the leash and let them research it. </p>
<p>How about this, assignment, there are three main theories of the origin of life and the universe, discover what they are, then using logic, reason and personal intuition write a thesis and both defend and oppose each of the three theories.  In your conclusion you may decided to make a final case for one of the prevailing theories or you may choose to leave the final question open.</p>
<p>Now I know this will piss some off, but I would bet that most of the people opposed to that one will be of the religious persuasion.  </p>
<p>Lets us add on to this though and consider the above assignment.</p>
<p>We told the student there are three prevailing theories they are of course </p>
<p>Pure Evolution<br />
Intelligent Design<br />
Pure Creationism</p>
<p>However, we did not tell them that, just the number was three and three shall the number be.  They would have to find these answers first on their own.  Then they would be required to examine each without the force of authority (state or church) and derive for themselves a true examination.</p>
<p>The paper would not be graded based on the individuals beliefs or conclusions.  Rather that each segment was understood and evaluated and dissected.  </p>
<p>Now what if this were how we handled most learning?  Not just issues that are highly debated?</p>
<p>Lastly, what if I could send my son to a school like that, what if you could send your son to a school like you described and Barngeek could send his kids to a school based on Christian faith (of his particular brand by the way).</p>
<p>What if the state got out of this business of education of our children?  What if we all had back all the property tax we paid as owners or via rent and were able to use that to see to our children&#8217;s education?  What if churches and frankly any group were free to create &#8220;schools&#8221; with no accountability to the state at all?</p>
<p>Why does Barngeek even have the right to bitch about this issue?  Because his money is taken from him, against his will and used to further something against his morals, that is the ONLY REASON WHY.</p>
<p>Like I said there are plenty of things taught in school that are against my morals.  Last year about 4,000 dollars of my hard earned money went directly to fund them and who knows how much went indirectly via Federal support of education.  </p>
<p>Again though may be we should be more concerned about our academic standings in the world and kids killing themselves and each other than we are about one old as time debate that will never be settled anyway.</p>
